{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489085","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489085"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:04:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:04:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"588"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/588"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.04,0.03,0.82,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"588"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96820"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/588"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"588"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79435"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"2823"},{"type":"tags","id":"3622"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2121"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2132"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15086"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42103"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43018"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44331"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45006"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96820","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96820"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 18-year-old Indigenous man presents to his Northern Territory General Practice with a two hour history of chest pain. The chest pain is central, sharp, and worse on deep inspiration. It does not radiate to his arm or jaw. The pain is of such severity that he was unable to go to work. He feels feverish and \u0027aches all over,\u0027 especially over his joints. He has also felt more short of breath for the past two days.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHe is otherwise in good health with no other medical conditions, apart from an upper respiratory tract infection six weeks ago that was managed symptomatically. He has no history of smoking, alcohol, recreational drug use, tattoos, and is not sexually active.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, his pulse is 80/min, blood pressure 110/60mmHg, respiratory rate 15/min, and temperature 38.1C. There is a faint pink macular rash with borders poorly defined over his torso and arms. There are soft nodules around both his elbows. Initial bloods show:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHb 135 g/L [115-155]\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWCC 7 x10^9/L [4.0-10.0]\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Infective endocarditis","Scarlet fever","Kawasaki disease","Acute rheumatic fever","Pharyngitis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient likely has \u003Cstrong\u003Eacute rheumatic fever\u003C/strong\u003E, as evidenced by joint pain, chest pain characteristic of pericarditis, nodules on his elbows, and rash (erythema marginatum). This contributes some of the diagnostic criteria for rheumatic fever, known as the \u0022JONES\u0022 criteria, shown below:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJoint pain\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EO (carditis)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENodules (rheumatic)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EErythema marginatum\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESydenham chorea\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough a \u003Cstrong\u003Epharyngitis\u003C/strong\u003E infection with streptococcus pyogenes a few weeks ago may be the cause of the rheumatic fever, acute rheumatic fever itself is the most likely current diagnosis of this patient\u0027s symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u003Cstrong\u003Enfective endocarditis\u003C/strong\u003E presents with fevers, rigors, and aches in joints, and signs of heart failure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKawasaki disease\u003C/strong\u003E presents with lymphadenopathy, an exfoliative rash, and fever.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EScarlett feve\u003C/strong\u003Er presents with a rash following a streptococcus pyogenes infection; however, does not have the characteristic symptoms of rheumatic fever as this patient does.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Jones criteria is used to diagnose acute rheumatic fever and consists of joint pain, carditis, nodules, erythema marginatum, and sydenham chorea."],"references":["Sika-Paotonu D, Beaton A, Raghu A, et al. Acute Rheumatic Fever and Rheumatic Heart Disease. 2017 Mar 10 [Updated 2017 Apr 3]. In: Ferretti JJ, Stevens DL, Fischetti VA, editors. Streptococcus pyogenes : Basic Biology to Clinical Manifestations [Internet]. Oklahoma City (OK): University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center; 2016-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK425394/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79435"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"588"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79435","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/79435"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-02T22:44:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-02T22:44:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"588"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96820"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links